text: Brynhild Grasmoen (January 7, 1929 - December 30, 2000) was an American alpine skier. She competed in two events at the 1948 Winter Olympics. ==References== Category:1929 births Category:2000 deaths Category:American female alpine skiers Category:Olympic alpine skiers of the United States Category:Alpine skiers at the 1948 Winter Olympics Category:People from Merced, California
